![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/4379f2c3-3a63-4293-824d-f0fcc1345b8c/ep210.jpg)

The final solo project for the OG 6 Avengers, Hawkeye on Disney+, has just finished its first season, but did it hit its mark? In a show that is definitely a love letter to the Matt Fraction & David Aja comic series, Hawkeye tackles survivor's guilt, hero worship, regret and redemption, all with a fun and cheery holiday backdrop. Join us as we talk about the live-action debut of Kate Bishop, debate THAT CAMEO, and try to predict the future of the Avenging Archer in this spoiler filled recap and review of Hawkeye Season 1!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
